    <summary>A minimalist physics-based terminal Pong game</summary>
    <description>
**pong-ball** is a minimalist, physics-based Pong game for the terminal.

- Sub-stepped continuous collision physics — the ball never tunnels through walls, even at top speed
- A spring-driven paddle you steer with the keyboard or the mouse
- Five restrained themes, three game modes, six power-ups, five difficulty phases
- A persistent local score history with an in-game leaderboard
- Pure Go, a single static binary, zero runtime dependencies

This package installs the official `pong-ball.exe` from the project's signed GitHub release and verifies its SHA-256 checksum.
    </description>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/subhadeeproy3902/pong-ball/releases</releaseNotes>
